<br>
Demon: Yes he does. It's grammatically correct, plus he enjoys the irony of the whole thing.<br>
<br>
Faerie: It may be grammatically correct, but that doesn't make it necessary.<br>
<br>
Demon: Is it right to allow someone to make mistakes without pointing them out? To deprive them of a chance to learn?<br>
<br>
Faerie: He has better things to do than to point out the shortcomings of others.<br>
<br>
Demon: He does? Like what?<br>
<br>
Faerie: Well, he could be hard at work, doing... something.<br>
<br>
